 Purpose

This workflow will use the java keytool to create a Java key store and generate a key pair and export the public key.  It will then create a trust store and import the public key into the newly created trust store.  Lastly it will create a certificate request that can then be send manually by a user to a Certificate Authority to be signed and later imported by a user into the existing trust store.


 Results verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The workflow results will indicate whether the creation was successful. Be sure to also perform the following steps\:

  
 Notification plan

Define who should be notified when the workflow succeeds and fails..
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Cert Location - Required\: Fully qualified directory path where the certificate and certificate request will be created. Example /opt/app/ssl/
    Dname Suffix - Required\: The suffix of the Distinguished Name (DN) that will uniquely identify an entity in an X.509 certificate. The CN will be generated off the server name. Example OU\=Software, O\=HP, L\=Fort Collins, ST\=Colorado, C\=US
    Hostname - Required\: This is the hostname or ip address that will be used to create the CN or common name. Example myserver.hp.com
    Java Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the JAVA_HOME that will be used to create ssl configuration using the keytool. Example /opt/app/jdk1.6.0_35.
    KeySize - Required\: Key size or length that will be used when creating the java key store.  Example 2048
    KeyStore Location - Required\: Fully qualified directory path where the java keystore will be created. Example /opt/app/ssl
    KeyStore Passphrase - Required\: Key store password that will be used to create the keystore and export certificate.
    PrivateKey Passphrase - Required\: Password used to protect the private key in the keystore.
    Root CA Alias - Required\: Name or label given to uniquely identify the Root CA in the truststore. Example rootca
    Root CA File Location - Required\: Fully qualified file path to where the Root CA is located. Example /opt/app/ssl/rootca.crt
    TrustStore Location - Required\: Fully qualified directory path where the java truststore will be created. Example /opt/app/ssl
    Validity - Required\: Specifies the length in days during which the certificate is valid. Example 365

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Intermediate CA Alias - Optional\: Name or label given to uniquely identify the Intermediate CA in the truststore. Example intermediateca
    Intermediate CA File Location - Optional\: Fully qualified file path to where the Intermediate CA is located. Example /opt/app/ssl/intermediateca.crt
